<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at the side of someone • on the side of someone</xh5><p> <i>at the side of someone</i>—(coll.) compared with another person: She is quite clever <u>at the side of</u> other girls.</p><p><i>on the side of someone—</i>giving support to smb. in a conflict, etc.: Despite Callas’ harsh nature, she was always <u>on the side of</u> her students.</p> </entry>
